The Monster Game
In this course, you'll be learning to write web applications. The way to start doing that is to write an application, The Monster Game. That's the subject of this lab. There are three purposes here: 1. To walk you through all of the elements of the Lively System 2. To have you build a real application 3. To show you the methodology behind building a real application -- build a little piece, test, build another piece, test,...pretty soon you're done. You won't completely understand everything you're doing in this lab, just as (the first time) you don't understand why you add a pinch of salt to help water boil. That's OK; in about eight weeks you'll understand everything and you'll be able to do it from scratch. The first thing to do is play the game, so you'll see what we're building...next slide
